"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-07-olympics-star-smashes-european-record-immediately-proposes-partner-paris-21379517\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Alice Finot had a day to remember on Tuesday as she broke the European record in the 3000m steeplechase and then immediately proposed to her partner who was in the stands at the Stade de France.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 5, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_and_Bob\", \"score\": 0.9984946053839417, \"rank\": 0.0015076642457459773, \"text\": \"Alice\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_and_Bob\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_and_Bob\"}, {\"begin\": 62, \"end\": 77, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.115643502110137e-14, \"text\": \"European record\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA\"}, {\"begin\": 178, \"end\": 193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French star missed out on a medal as she finished fourth but it was an immense performance from her, setting a personal best and the fastest time ever by a European in the women's race.\", \"from\": 196, \"to\": 385, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 200, \"end\": 206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.889425096847309, \"rank\": 0.11553292973758503, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After celebrating on the track Finot headed over to the stands where her partner was waiting and Bruno Marti\\u0301nez Bargiela had the surprise of his life.\", \"from\": 387, \"to\": 538, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Finot got down on one knee and asked her boyfriend to marry her, presenting a pin rather than a ring and she explained why afterwards.\", \"from\": 540, \"to\": 674, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow all the action from Paris 2024 on our live Olympics blog.\", \"from\": 676, \"to\": 740, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 703, \"end\": 713, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999997492068, \"rank\": 2.5079945616847125e-10, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'I told myself that if I ran under nine minutes, knowing that nine is my lucky number and that we have been together for nine years, then I would propose,' Finot said, having cross the line in eight minutes and 58.67seconds.\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 966, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'I do not like doing things like everyone else.\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 1015, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Since he had not done it yet, I told myself that maybe it was up to me to do it.\", \"from\": 1016, \"to\": 1096, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So, I gave a pin that I ran with to my boyfriend.\", \"from\": 1097, \"to\": 1146, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On it, it says: \\\"Love is in Paris.\\\"\", \"from\": 1147, \"to\": 1182, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1175, \"end\": 1180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999997025952, \"rank\": 2.974839862495121e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'He's the one who always gives me strength and if I managed to get under nine minutes, that meant a lot.'\", \"from\": 1184, \"to\": 1289, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thankfully for the sake of Finot and to avoid the most awkward moment in Olympic history, Marti\\u0301nez Bargiela said yes and completed a great day for the Frenchwoman.\", \"from\": 1291, \"to\": 1455, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Of her performance on the track, she said: 'I really had a blast, I managed to express myself.\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1551, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'It was just a tiny bit (that was) missing to get a medal, I am sorry.\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1623, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I do not regret anything.'\", \"from\": 1624, \"to\": 1654, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bahrain's Winfred Yavi won the gold with an Olympic record time of 8:52.76, ahead of Uganda's Peruth Chemutai who took silver and Kenya's Faith Cherotich with bronze.\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1822, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1656, \"end\": 1663, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bahrain\", \"score\": 0.7558462673309019, \"rank\": 0.2883033710318449, \"text\": \"Bahrain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bahrain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bahrain\"}, {\"begin\": 1666, \"end\": 1678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Winfred_Yavi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Winfred Yavi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Winfred_Yavi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Winfred_Yavi\"}, {\"begin\": 1741, \"end\": 1747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"score\": 0.9999999787698928, \"rank\": 1.9791673570444706e-08, \"text\": \"Uganda\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A memory that will last a lifetime for Alice Finot and her husband to be \\u00f0\\u009f\\u00ab\\u00b6\\u00e2\\u009d\\u00a4\\u00ef\\u00b8\\u008f\\u00f0\\u009f\\u00a5\\u00b9#paris2024#olympicspic.twitter.com/BqFRfzWFdq  For more stories like this,check our sport page.\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 2006, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Metro Sport for the latest news onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram.\", \"from\": 2008, \"to\": 2078, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:How many sports and medals are there at the Paris 2024 Olympics?\", \"from\": 2080, \"to\": 2154, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:Tony Hawk responds to calls to make stunning Olympics comeback  ArrowMORE:Why is there a motorbike on the track cycling at the Olympics?\", \"from\": 2156, \"to\": 2302, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.\", \"from\": 2304, \"to\": 2414, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply.\", \"from\": 2416, \"to\": 2547, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.\", \"from\": 2548, \"to\": 2720, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2610, \"end\": 2616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punchy,_Somme\", \"score\": 0.6784377202962604, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Punchy\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punchy,_Somme\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punchy,_Somme\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply.\", \"from\": 2722, \"to\": 2853, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy\", \"from\": 2854, \"to\": 2914, \"entities\": []}]}"